                "languageCode": "en",
                "name": "Praise & Positive Reinforcement",
                "buttonColor": "#ED1651"
            },
            "contentSections": [
                {
                    "elements": [
                        {
                            "type": "TEXT",
                            "text": "Praise your children when they are behaving well! They may not show it but you'll see them doing that good behaviour again…\n"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "TEXT",
                            "text": "Praise works for our children, too. When you bring more attention to positive behaviour, they are likely to do it more often. They also will feel good about themselves!"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "LIST",
                            "items": [
                                {
                                    "heading": "Step 1. Praise your teenager for something they have done well",
                                    "body": "They may not show it, but you’ll see them doing that good thing again. It will also reassure them that you notice and care."
                                },
                                {
                                    "heading": "Step 2. Praise the behaviour",
                                    "body": "Use words to describe the behaviour that you are praising. Say \"Well done for finishing all your chores, Sam\", instead of \"Good job\"."
                                },
                                {
                                    "heading": "Step 3. Praise with enthusiasm",
                                    "body": "Really mean it when you say it!\nTry to find 3 things that you can praise your children for every day. \nYou can also praise other adults in your household, too. Notice how they respond!"
                                }
                            ]
                        }
